Actors module setup includes pekko-testkit in test scope; it provides TestKit/TestProbe utilities needed for reliable actor message and lifecycle assertions.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"Target current Pekko 2.0 classic actor APIs such as ActorSystem, Props, AbstractActor, serialization/configuration, and TestKit/TestProbe. Do not use the removed deprecated org.apache.pekko.actor.TypedActor, TypedActorExtension, or TypedProps APIs that existed in 1.1.5. If tests exercise Java serialization, configure pekko.actor.allow-java-serialization = on and disable serializer warnings in the ActorSystem config. If tests exercise DnsSettings/sun.net.dns integration, add --add-exports=java.base/sun.net.dns=ALL-UNNAMED to both JVM test args and native-image build args.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"Adding pekko-testkit broadens the test classpath; tests should use it only as a harness and keep assertions focused on pekko-actor behavior.\",\n    \"The current failure appears to be stale coverage of APIs removed in Pekko 2.0-M1, not a missing dependency.\",\n    \"Pekko 2.0.0-M1 is an experimental milestone and removed a large amount of deprecated code, so API drift from 1.1.5 is likely.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0e7964c7642baff4016a407b2e8ba48194944d8bdd9b7b10c8\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1322, "output": 927, "cacheRead": 26624, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 28873, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782610725707, "responseId": "resp_0e7964c7642baff4016a407b26303c8194ba6773f24452a253"}}
